cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.AR, cs.CE

This paper focuses on Multi-access Edge Computing (MEC) in the context of 5G networks, which involves network infrastructure and communication protocols. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the use of virtualization and distributed computing, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper proposes a statistical model and discusses performance optimization, which could be categorized under cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
